item.title: Smartphone stand - toilet paper stand
item.description:
I have a toilet paper stand from Wenko, like seen here:

https://www.amazon.de/WENKO-Stand-WC-Garnitur-Rivalta-WC-B%C3%BCrstenhalter/dp/B07PJCTDVZ

For longer sessions or for not being forced to stop watching some YouTube or 9gag videos, this Smartphone stand is perfect.

The picture shows that for the iPhone 7, the holder is a bit too large, but the size fits perfectly for my OnePlus 9 Pro. So also think of your guests ;-)

The design fits very tightly, so this is really robust without any wobbling.

Have fun!

item.title: Boston Bottle coozy
item.description: This is a Boston bottle holder suitable for shipping. The Boston bottle is a standard size. I use a 1/4 inch bubble wrap on most of the body. item.title: Parameterized Power Strip Mount
item.description:
This is a fully parameterized mount for power strips.

I found some designs here, but none fitted the strips I had at home.

The .3mf file provided is just an example, and will fit a power strip with the following dimensions:
Width: 53mm
Height: 41mm

To customize, you will need OpenScad and the dimensions of you power strip (just measure them but account for a little clearance, .5mm worked for me). Then get the .scad file, open it and fill in your dimensions at the top. Make sure the mount is not to wide, so it will not cover any power sockets and make sure the power cord will fit through the hole (there are parameters for those dimensions, too). All dimensions are in millimeters.

item.title: Prusa i3 direct extruder with Ender 3 metal extruder
item.description:
I added a direct extruder mount that reuses the metal extruder from the Ender 3, because this is VERY cheap, and it's available from all suppliers. I also rotated the motor placement to prevent the motor from hitting the frame, which increases the print volume compared to some other direct extruders I found.

The generator is included here, but newer versions (if any) will be uploaded here:
https://github.com/dc740/Roadfeldt_3d_hczf_mount

How to use:

Open the files in OpenSCAD and pick: Carriage: Prusa i3 Extruder: Standard metal extruders
Pick the rest of the configuration to match your components, and generate the STL.

Features:
Direct extruder
Easy to make
Easy to repair
Keeps the printing volume

item.title: EVA fan duct for Kingroon KP3S Titan (1st version)
item.description:
This is a remix of the EVA ventilation adapted to the Kingroon KP3s Titan (1st version).
The files are still being worked on, they may be subject to changes and updates

OPTION A
hotend V6 (fan low V6 / support 5015 / arm carriage)

OPTION B
hotend V6 Volcano (fan V6 volcano / support 5015 / arm carriage)

OPTION C
My current setup with bi-metal Mellow throat 2.1mm longer than the original one. I like having more space between the ventilation and the heated bed.

hotend V6 (fan OPTION C/ support OPTION C / arm OPTION C)

TRIHORN
TriHorn, latest ventilation released for EVA

hotend V6 (TriHorn fan / TriHorn support 5015 / TriHorn arm)

W.I.P.
Screw M3, nuts M3

Print Settings
Brims/Rafts ─ OPTIONAL
Supports ─ Doesn't Matter
Wall Thickness ─ ≥1.2mm
Top/Bottom Thickness ─ ≥1.2mm
Infill ─ 30%
Filament material:
PETG, ABS, CPE-HG100, ASA, PETG carbon

Notes:
I recommend 4 wall/perimeters for the heat-insert.

item.title: Fish Stick Trainer
item.description: This is a device used to train a fish to do tricks. I've read you can teach betta fish many cool tricks so I designed this. You place a treat at the end in the little pocket and press the top to release the food to feed the fish. The idea is that you fist show your fish that food comes from the stick, then it will start to follow it around, and then you can make it go through hoops or chicanes, and finally on command!

item.title: Shock Absorber, 60 mm Disc (TPU)
item.description:
Shock absorber for vibration reduction.

Suitable for something vibrates which has a flat bottom like speakers, NAS, 3D printers.

You should print 2 of them and glue flat faces together.

Print Settings :

Layer height - 0.15 to 0.2 mm
Infill density - 100%, preferably
Material - elastic filaments like TPU, I recommend filaments that have shore hardness less than 90A.

item.title: Case for W1209 Temperature Control Switch
item.description:
Needed a case for my temperature control switch (12V) W1209.
W1209 are available in 5, 12, 24V (maybe more). In my case I used one common 12VDC source and connected the relay contacts to switch my (noisy) cooling fan on and off.
Pretty simple.

Tip: I used four M3 "Brass Heat Set Inserts" but only used two screws in the rear. The front screws are too high for the lid. So you may save two brass inserts.
